message.content:
A Rosa bracteata is a species of climbing rose native to China.
It has elegant, arching stems and can grow up to 6 meters in length.
The flowers of Rosa bracteata bloom in early summer and are usually white to cream in color with yellow centers.
The blooms have a delicate fragrance and are surrounded by large, showy bracts that are pinkish-white in color.
The leaves of Rosa bracteata are glossy and deep green in color, with pointed tips and toothed edges.
This plant is often used in landscapes as a climbing ornamental, and is also grown for its medicinal properties.
Rosa bracteata is often found in temperate and subtropical climates and is best grown in full sun with well-drained soil.
